article.headline: Robert Morris 70, St. Francis (Pa.) 56
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Coron Williams scored 18 points, including knocking down four 3-pointers, to lead Robert Morris past St. Francis (Pa.) 70-56 on Saturday night. Velton Jones added 13 points, Mike McFadden 11 and Russell Johnson 10 for the Colonials (19-8, 10-4 Northeast Conference), who have won three straight games. Robert Morris also beat St. Francis on Wednesday in the only other regular-season meeting. Robert Morris opened on a 22-10 run, led by 11 at the break and outscored the Red Flash 33-30 in the second half to seal it. The Red Flash outshot the Colonials from the floor (48.9 percent to 45.1 percent), but Robert Morris got the best of St. Francis from the foul line (78.3 percent to 50 percent). The Colonials also forced 24 Red Flash turnovers en route to victory. Earl Brown finished with 17 points to lead St. Francis (5-20, 4-10), who have lost six in a row.
